    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I made these in mini muffin cups as I couldn&#39;t cut nice, neat squares with my first batch. It was much easier and cuter. I reserved some of the fruit &#038; nuts and sprinkled it on top before chilling. (Ina Garten does this with chocolate bark in her new book). I used candied ginger, salted peanuts, almonds, dried cherries, golden raisins and fleur de sel. Absolutely adorable &#038; delicious &#8211; thanks for the inspiration.</p>
    </div>

