      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=1561#comment-5157' data-commentid="5157" data-postid="1561" data-belowelement="comment-5157" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-5158" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=1561#comment-5158"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-12-16T22:46:43-05:00">Tuesday, December 16, 2014 at 10:46 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Gosh I&#39;m late to the party! Just made these with dark chocolate, dried apricot paste (chopped up), dried cranberries, toasted cashews, and toasted walnuts.</p>
<p>Now I&#39;m thinking of a rocky road version with marshmallow and pecans. My question is this:</p>
<p>Do you think chopped-up petit beurre biscuits would stand up to this treatment?</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=1561#comment-5158' data-commentid="5158" data-postid="1561" data-belowelement="comment-5158" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-5159" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
